obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line 2
  line `THE ACQUISITION OF CERTAIN AREA AT AYODHYA ACT, 1993`
  line `A CT N O. 33 OF 1993`
  line `[3 rd April, 1993.]`
  line `An Act to provide for the acquisition of certain area at Ayodhya and for matters connected`
  line `therewith or incidental thereto.`
  line `W HEREAS there has been a long-standing dispute relating to the structure (including the premises of`
  line `the inner and outer courtyards of such structure), commonly known as the Ram Janma Bhumi-Babri`
  line `Masjid, situated in village Kot Ramchandra in Ayodhya, in Pargana Haveli Avadh, in tehsil Faizabad`
  line `Sadar, in the district of Faizabad of the State of Uttar Pradesh;`
  line `A ND WHEREAS the said dispute has affected the maintenance of public order and harmony between`
  line `different communities in the country;`
  line `A ND WHEREAS it is necessary to maintain public order and to promote communal harmony and the`
  line `spirit of common brotherhood amongst the people of India;`
  line `A ND WHEREAS with a view to achieving the aforesaid objectives, it is necessary to acquire certain`
  line `areas in Ayodhya;`
  line `B E it enacted by Parliament in the Forty-fourth Year of the Republic of India as follows: —`
  line `CHAPTER I`
  line `P RELIMINARY`
  line `1. Short title and commencement. — ( 1 ) This Act may be called the Acquisition of Certain Area at`
  line `Ayodhya Act, 1993.`
  line `( 2 ) It shall be deemed to have come into force on the 7th day of January, 1993.`
  line `2. Definitions. — In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires, —`
  line `( a ) “area” means the area (including all the buildings, structures or other properties comprised`
  line `therein) specified in the Schedule;`
  line `( b ) “authorised person” means a person or body of persons or trustees of any trust authorised by`
  line `the Central Government under section 7;`
  line `( c ) “Claims Commissioner” means the Claims Commissioner appointed under sub-section ( 2 ) of`
  line `section 8;`
  line `( d ) “prescribed” means prescribed by rules made under this Act.`
  line `CHAPTER II`
  line `A CQUISITION OF THE AREA IN AYODHYA`
  line `3. Acquisition of rights in respect of certain area. — On and from the commencement of this Act,`
  line `the right, title and interest in relation to the area shall, by virtue of this Act, stand transferred to, and vest`
  line `in, the Central Government.`
  line `4. General effect of vesting. — ( 1 ) The area shall be deemed to include all assets, rights, leaseholds,`
  line `powers, authority and privileges and all property, movable and immovable, including lands, buildings,`
  line `structures, shops of whatever nature or other properties and all other rights and interests in, or arising out`
  line `of, such properties as were immediately before the commencement of this Act in the ownership,`
  line `possession, power or control of any person or the State Government of Uttar Pradesh, as the case may be,`
  line `and all registers, maps, plans, drawings and other documents of whatever nature relating thereto.`
  line `( 2 ) All properties aforesaid which have vested in the Central Government under section 3 shall, by`
  line `force of such vesting, be freed and discharged from any trust, obligation, mortgage, charge, lien and all`
  line `other encumbrances affecting them and any attachment, injunction, decree or order of any court or`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-3
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Page 3`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  sourcePage 3
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line 3
  line `tribunal or other authority restricting the use of such properties in any manner or appointing any receiver`
  line `in respect of the whole or any part of such properties shall cease to have any effect.`
  line `( 3 ) If, on the commencement of this Act, any suit, appeal or other proceeding in respect of the right,`
  line `title and interest relating to any property which has vested in the Central Government under section 3, is`
  line `pending before any court, tribunal or other authority, the same shall abate.`
  line `5. Duty of person or State Government in charge of the management of the area to deliver all`
  line `assets, etc. — ( 1 ) The Central Government may take all necessary steps to secure possession of the area`
  line `which is vested in that Government under section 3.`
  line `( 2 ) On the vesting of the area in the Central Government under section 3, the person or State`
  line `Government of Uttar Pradesh, as the case may be, in charge of the management of the area immediately`
  line `before such vesting shall be bound to deliver to the Central Government or the authorised person, all`
  line `assets, registers and other documents in their custody relating to such vesting or where it is not practicable`
  line `to deliver such registers or documents, the copies of such registers or documents authenticated in the`
  line `prescribed manner.`
  line `6. Power of Central Government to direct vesting of the area in another authority or body or`
  line `trust. — ( 1 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sections 3, 4, 5 and 7, the Central Government may, if`
  line `it is satisfied that any authority or other body, or trustees of any trust, set up on or after the`
  line `commencement of this Act is or are willing to comply with such terms and conditions as that Government`
  line `may think fit to impose, direct by notification in the Official Gazette, that the right, title and interest or`
  line `any of them in relation to the area or any part thereof, instead of continuing to vest in the Central`
  line `Government, vest in that authority or body or trustees of that trust either on the date of the notification or`
  line `on such later date as may be specified in the notification.`
  line `( 2 ) When any right, title and interest in relation to the area or part thereof vest in the authority or body`
  line `or trustees referred to in sub-section ( 1 ), such rights of the Central Government in relation to such area or`
  line `part thereof, shall, on and from the date of such vesting, be deemed to have become the rights of that`
  line `authority or body or trustees of that trust.`
  line `( 3 ) The provisions of sections 4, 5, 7 and 11 shall, so far as may be, apply in relation to such`
  line `authority or body or trustees as they apply in relation to the Central Government and for this purpose`
  line `references therein to the Central Government shall be construed as references to such authority or body or`
  line trustees.
  line `CHAPTER III`
  line `M ANAGEMENT AND ADMINISTRATION OF PROPERTY`
  line `7. Management of property by Government. — ( 1 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in any`
  line `contract or instrument or order of any court, tribunal or other authority to the contrary, on and from the`
  line `commencement of this Act, the property vested in the Central Government under section 3 shall be`
  line `managed by the Central Government or by a person or body of persons or trustees of any trust authorised`
  line `by that Government in this behalf.`
  line `( 2 ) In managing the property vested in the Central Government under section 3, the Central`
  line `Government or the authorised person shall ensure that the position existing before the commencement of`
  line `this Act in the area on which the structure (including the premises of the inner and outer courtyards of`
  line `such structure), commonly known as the Ram Janma Bhumi-Babri Masjid, stood in village Kot`
  line `Ramchandra in Ayodhya, in Pargana Haveli Avadh, in tehsil Faizabad Sadar, in the district of Faizabad of`
  line `the State of Uttar Pradesh is maintained.`
  line `CHAPTER IV`
  line `M ISCELLANEOUS`
  line `8. Payment of amount. — ( 1 ) The owner of any land, building, structure or other property comprised`
  line `in the area shall be given by the Central Government, for the transfer to and vesting in that Government`
  line `under section 3 of that land, building, structure or other property, in cash an amount equivalent to the`
  line `market value of the land, building, structure or other property.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-4
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Page 4`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  sourcePage 4
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line 4
  line `( 2 ) The Central Government shall, for the purpose of deciding the claim of the owner or any person`
  line `having a claim against the owner under sub-section ( 1 ), by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint a`
  line `Claims Commissioner.`
  line `( 3 ) The Claims Commissioner shall regulate his own procedure for receiving and deciding the claims.`
  line `( 4 ) The owner or any person having a claim against the owner may make a claim to the Claims`
  line `Commissioner within a period of ninety days from the date of commencement of this Act:`
  line `Provided that if the Claims Commissioner is satisfied that the claimant was prevented by sufficient`
  line `cause from preferring the claim within the said period of ninety days, the Claims Commissioner may`
  line `entertain the claim within a further period of ninety days and not thereafter.`
  line `9. Act to override all other enactments. — The provisions of this Act shall have effect`
  line `notwithstanding anything inconsistent therewith contained in any other law for the time being in force or`
  line `any instrument having effect by virtue of any law other than this Act or any decree or order of any court,`
  line `tribunal or other authority.`
  line `10. Penalties. — Any person who is in charge of the management of the area and fails to deliver to the`
  line `Central Government or the authorised person any asset, register or other document in his custody relating`
  line `to such area or, as the case may be, authenticated copies of such register or document, shall be punishable`
  line `with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three years or with fine which may extend to ten`
  line `thousand rupees or with both.`
  line `11. Protection of action taken in good faith. — No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against the Central Government or the authorised person or any of the officers or other employees of`
  line `that Government or the authorised person for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done`
  line `under this Act.`
  line `12. Power to make rules. — ( 1 ) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules to carry out the provisions of this Act.`
  line `( 2 ) Every rule made by the Central Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it`
  line `is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which`
  line `may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the`
  line `session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that rule.`
  line `13. Repeal and saving. — ( 1 ) Subject to the provisions of sub-section ( 2 ), the Acquisition of Certain`
  line `Area at Ayodhya Ordinance, 1993 ( Ord. 8 of 1993), is hereby repealed.`
  line `( 2 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in the said Ordinance, —`
  line `( a ) the right, title and interest in relation to plot No. 242 situated in village Kot Ramchandra`
  line `specified against Sl. No. 1 of the Schedule to the said Ordinance shall be deemed never to have been`
  line `transferred to, and vested in, the Central Government;`
  line `( b ) any suit, appeal or other proceeding in respect of the right, title and interest relating to the said`
  line `plot No. 242, pending before any court, tribunal or other authority, shall be deemed never to have`
  line `abated and such suit, appeal or other proceeding (including the orders or interim orders of any court`
  line `thereon) shall be deemed to have been restored to the position existing immediately before the`
  line `commencement of the said Ordinance;`
  line `( c ) any other action taken or thing done under that Ordinance in relation to the said plot No. 242`
  line `shall be deemed never to have been taken or done.`
  line `( 3 ) Notwithstanding such repeal, anything done or any action taken under the said Ordinance shall be`
  line `deemed to have been done or taken under the corresponding provisions of this Act.`
